# ============================================================================
# Ten Lifetimes — PUBLIC production repo.
# Belt-and-suspenders: the repo is assembled from a docs-only tree, but these
# rules guarantee no media or private assets are ever committed.
# ============================================================================

# --- Media: audio / video / images / project files ---
*.mp3
*.wav
*.flac
*.aif
*.aiff
*.mp4
*.mov
*.mkv
*.avi
*.webm
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.png
*.webp
*.gif
*.tif
*.tiff
*.bmp
*.psd
*.ai
*.aep
*.prproj
*.zip
*.7z
*.rar

# --- Private asset folders (reference photos, masters, master refs) ---
01_Reference_Gary/
02_Reference_Jen/
03_Couple_Photos/
16_Master_References/

# --- Per-chapter media subfolders ---
*/Stills/
*/Motion/
*/Final/
*/References/

# --- EXCEPTION: review dailies are intentionally PUBLIC for Gemini GVR ---
# EP decision 2026-06-26: generated review stills are committed to 12_Dailies/
# so the VFX reviewer (Gemini) can access them from the repo.
!12_Dailies/**/*.png
!12_Dailies/**/*.jpg
!12_Dailies/**/*.jpeg

# --- EXCEPTION: Production_History is the public ILM-style learning archive ---
# EP decision 2026-06-26 (full archive): superseded/rejected renders are KEPT and
# published with their .md provenance as institutional memory for Continuum.
# These two folders are the ONLY places media is permitted; all else stays on the NAS.
!13_Production_History/**/*.png
!13_Production_History/**/*.jpg
!13_Production_History/**/*.jpeg

# --- Tooling / environments / OS cruft ---
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
